      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must demonstrate correct implementation of governing equations through at least one benchmark problem with known analytical solution.",
      "rationale": "The Navier-Stokes solver was verified against the lid-driven cavity benchmark (Re = 1000) and the Poiseuille flow analytical solution. Errors were within 0.5% of reference values, confirming correct numerical implementation of the momentum equations used in the hemolysis prediction workflow."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) must be less than 5% for the primary quantity of interest (volume-averaged hemolysis index) using Richardson extrapolation across at least three mesh refinement levels.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study yielded GCI of 1.8% for the volume-averaged hemolysis index using Richardson extrapolation (refinement ratio r = 1.5). Fine-grid solution used for all production runs. Discretization error is well within the 5% acceptance threshold for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
