      "acceptanceCriteria": "The primary QoI (relative hemolysis index) must be directly linked to the clinical endpoint and regulatory acceptance criterion.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index (RH) is the quantity used in FDA guidance for comparative hemolysis assessment of blood-contacting devices. RH < 1 directly maps to the regulatory acceptance criterion. The QoI is clinically meaningful and directly supports the COU decision."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
